Who controls the internet? Increasingly, the answer is large corporations and governments -- a trend that&#039;s threatening digital privacy and access to information online, says web developer Tamas Kocsis. In this informative talk, Kocsis breaks down the different threats to internet freedom and shares his plan to build an alternative, decentralized network that returns power to everyday users.

This talk was presented at a TED Salon event given in partnership with Samsung. TED editors featured it among our selections on the home page. Read more about TED Salons.

